# Edge case: state wildcard `~?` on LHS, fixed state on RHS
# Tests:  a rule pattern with `s~?` matches any defined state (the
#         wildcard collapses the state-dependent dispatch).  Combined
#         with a fixed RHS state, the rule "resets" the component to a
#         known value regardless of incoming state.  RM's StateChange
#         op carries a new_state_index that resolves the new state
#         from the rule body; the LHS wildcard means
#         pc.required_state_index == -1 on the reactant side, so RM
#         must NOT skip embeddings whose component holds a non-default
#         state.  The existing ft_state_wildcards.bngl uses ~? for
#         observation; this model uses it on the rule side, which is a
#         distinct code path through count_embeddings_single's state
#         filter.
# Edge:   four-state component with three different "modified" states
#         all collapsing to one canonical state via the wildcard rule.
# Tier:   base
# Expected: at long time A_canon dominates (all populations funnel into S0).

begin model
begin parameters
    A_tot   60
    k_drift 0.10   # /s, S0 -> any other (uniform)
    k_reset 0.20   # /s, any-state-but-S0 -> S0
end parameters

begin molecule types
    A(s~S0~S1~S2~S3)
end molecule types

begin seed species
    A(s~S0)  A_tot
end seed species

begin observables
    Molecules  A_total  A()
    Molecules  A_S0     A(s~S0)
    Molecules  A_S1     A(s~S1)
    Molecules  A_S2     A(s~S2)
    Molecules  A_S3     A(s~S3)
    Molecules  A_any    A(s~?)
end observables

begin reaction rules
    # Drift outward — three explicit transitions populate non-S0 states.
    A(s~S0) -> A(s~S1)  k_drift
    A(s~S0) -> A(s~S2)  k_drift
    A(s~S0) -> A(s~S3)  k_drift
    # The reset rule: state wildcard on LHS matches any state, and the
    # exclusion against S0 below funnels only modified states to S0.
    # NFsim's NFprop2 implementation expands the wildcard rule into
    # per-state instances; RM should match the wildcard directly on
    # the reactant pattern.
    A(s~?) -> A(s~S0)  k_reset  exclude_reactants(1,A(s~S0))
end reaction rules
end model

begin actions
simulate({method=>"nf",t_end=>40,n_steps=>80})
end actions
